    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "Offering a driver-spec 997.1 Carrera featuring the high-revving 3.6L naturally aspirated flat-six engine. This unit is mated to a tactile 6-speed manual transaxle, delivering power through a precise rear-wheel-drive configuration. The chassis remains tight, utilizing its multi-link rear geometry and MacPherson struts to provide the communicative feedback Porsche is known for. Noteworthy mechanical updates include a documented IMS bearing retrofit and a fresh rear main seal, addressing critical longevity concerns for the M96/M97 architecture. The hydraulic steering rack is leak-free, providing exceptional weighting through the corners. While the exterior shows minor road-going patina, the mechanical vitals\u2014including oil pressure and cooling efficiency\u2014are within factory spec. A robust example for the purist seeking performance over shelf-queen status.",
